New Records: David Willey finishes his career with 100 wickets at 29.75 across 73 ODIs
Key Match Events: David Willey finished his ODI career with 3 for 56
Haris Rauf and Mohammad Wasim had a last-wicket partnership of 53 off 32 balls
Agha Salman scored an impressive half-century from 42 deliveries
Adil Rashid became England’s leading wicket-taker in the tournament with 14 wickets

David Willey took Abdullah Shafique's wicket with his second ball
Pre-Game Insights: Jos Buttler decided to bat first after winning the toss
England were unchanged from their victory over the Netherlands, while Pakistan made one change with Shadab Khan replacing Hasan Ali
Post-Match Reflections: Babar Azam acknowledged Pakistan's mistakes in batting, bowling, and fielding throughout the competition and committed to facilitating the rebuild
Jos Buttler reflected on the emotional significance of the win despite a disappointing tournament
David Willey expressed pride in his career and reflected on his retirement decision
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan needed to chase their target of 338 in 6.4 overs to finish in the top four
